spontaneous symmetry breaking, topology, and universal low-energy behavior. Advanced topics including Berry phase, renormalization group, Green’s functions, quantum entanglement, tensor-network concepts, topological order, gauge theory, and quantum thermalization will also be introduced. Emphasis is placed not only on computational techniques, but also on the organizing principles that enable complex quantum matter to exhibit robust emergent phenomena. The course aims to provide graduate students with the conceptual and technical foundation necessary to engage with contemporary research in condensed matter physics and quantum many-body theory.","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"oxBSqJy63u"}],"key":"fx7xFpQ7sd"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"References","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"key":"ugSC0sDBRr"}],"identifier":"references","label":"References","html_id":"references","implicit":true,"key":"opYSOSvyCB"},{"type":"list","ordered":true,"start":1,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Chaikin and Lubensky, Principles of Condensed Matter Physics","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"key":"bYtM73fi6c"}],"key":"N657ml4s91"}],"key":"Wv2CbtYjn9"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Piers Coleman, Introduction to Many-Body Physics","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"wUCSP9EbvS"}],"key":"lfota1EmDL"}],"key":"jNPy8WM2j3"},{"type":"listI